Commented on #64937 C# EditorPlugin with List<T> crashes editor on C# solution rebuild

It seems like Godot indiscriminately marshals C# collections -- even if the element type of the collection is unmarshallable. When fields/properties aren't marshalled, the C# memory gets corrupted leading to an eventual crash of the editor after enough solution rebuilds.
Commented on #64937 C# EditorPlugin with List<T> crashes editor on C# solution rebuild

I was running a VS debugger on the editor when it crashed and it seems like the crash causes by incorrect memory access.
Not sure if this is the cause or the result of marshalling problems.
